3. The Group Admin Dashboard (Unit Owners)
â€¢ Single & Bulk Invites: A form to invite a single guest (with a "Needs Parking?" checkbox), plus a CSV upload button to generate bulk invites for business meetings.
â€¢ Unit-Specific Audit Logs: A private view where owners only see the entry/exit history of their specific guests.
â€¢ Access Management Controls: Buttons to instantly Revoke/Cancel a guest's pass early, or Resend/Refresh the welcome link if a guest loses their SMS/email.
â€¢ Long-Term Credential Requests: A form for owners to request permanent STid mobile Bluetooth credentials for new long-term tenants or staff.
4. The Guard Dashboard (Underground Parking)
â€¢ Filtered Parking Roster: A read-only screen showing only today's expected visitors who checked the "Needs Parking" box.
â€¢ Manual Boom Gate Override: A button to manually log a guest in and trigger the Impro relay to open the parking gate if their phone dies.
â€¢ Quick-Call Directory: A built-in digital phonebook so the guard can instantly call a specific apartment or business to approve an unannounced delivery driver.
5. The Guest Experience (Mobile Web App)
â€¢ Dynamic QR Code Generation: The app generates a unique random number converted into a QR code, formatted perfectly to act as a Wiegand string for the ZKTeco QR600HK readers.
â€¢ The Digital Guidebook: The QR code sits on a mobile page that also displays the unit's Check-in/Check-out times, House Rules, and the Wi-Fi password.
â€¢ Backup PIN Code: The page provides a fallback numeric PIN that guests can type into the QR600HK keypad if their screen is cracked or won't scan.
6. Behind-the-Scenes Hardware & Network Logic
â€¢ API Credential Pushing: The Next.js backend automatically pushes the newly generated QR string via the Impro API into the TAG_CODE field as tag type 15.
â€¢ Automated Expiration: The system automatically revokes the credential via the API the minute the guest's booking ends.
â€¢ API Retry Queue: If the building's internet tunnel drops, the Supabase database queues the newly generated QR codes and pushes them to the Impro hardware the second the internet reconnects.
â€¢ Anti-Passback / Single-Use Logic: The system strictly prevents a guest from scanning their QR code, walking in, and passing a screenshot of it to a friend outside.
â€¢ Lift Segregation: Automated logic ensuring an Airbnb guest's code only unlocks the lift for their specific residential floor, restricting them from commercial levels.
